    • getClass

      public <T> Class<? extends T> getClass​(T[] param)
      Returns the component type Class for the specified value.
      1. If the specified value is not an array, the specified value's direct Class is returned.
      2. If the specified value is an array, the specified array's component type is returned.
      3. This method does not work with any type of List.

        In other words, if the specified value is a List or other data structure type, the Class of that data structure is returned.

      Type Parameters:
      T - The value type of the Class being returned.
      Parameters:
      param - The value. Does not have to be an array.
      Returns:
      The component type Class for the specified value.

    • getArrayClass

      @SafeVarargs public final <T> Class getArrayClass​(T... param)
      Returns the array Class for the specified value.

      The intended use of this method is to pass a value that is not an array into this method. Because of the nature of varargs, the array Class of the specified value will be returned.

      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of value being returned.
      Parameters:
      param - The value.
      Returns:
      The array Class for the specified value.

    • getWOSimpleName

      @Deprecated public String getWOSimpleName​(Object obj)
      Deprecated.
      Returns the "work-around" simple name of the specified Object.

      Returns the String "Null" if the specified Object is null.
      The returned String will never itself be null.

      This method was created as a work-around for inconsistencies present when obfuscation was applied in the original TRiBot client.
      Should no longer be necessary in TRiBot FX, but is being kept just in case.

      Parameters:
      obj - The Object.
      Returns:
      The simple name of the specified Object.

    • instanceOf

      public boolean instanceOf​(Object t, Class... cs)
      Checks if the specified Object is an instance of any of the specified Classes.

      If the specified Object is assignable from any of the specified classes, this method returns true. In other words, the specified Object can be an instance of a child class.

      Parameters:
      t - The Object being compared.
      cs - The Classes being compared.
      Returns:
      if the specified Object is an instance of any of the specified Classes, false otherwise.
